Differential diagnosis . The new species differs from P. gr a t a by the dorsal position of the suranal plate (vs. ventral in P. gr a t a ); by 2 pairs of the aggenital setae (vs. 3 pairs in
P. grata
), and by distinctly shorter dorsal idiosomal setae c 1 , d 1 , d 2 , e 1 , and e 2 ( 10–16 vs. 20–53 in P. g r at a ).
